### 4. Admin Control Panel Updates

#### [MODIFY] [page.js](file:///c:/Users/hp/Desktop/work/karyabandhu_portfolio/Karayabandhu%20Pvt%20Ltd%20project/app/admin/page.js)

##### **Issue 1: Resume Link**
- In the Candidate Hub modal, wrap the displayed resume file name with a clickable link pointing to `reviewCandidate.credentials.fileUrl`, opening it in a new tab:
  ```javascript
  <a href={reviewCandidate.credentials.fileUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" className="...">
    📄 {reviewCandidate.credentials.fileName}
  </a>
  ```

##### **Issue 2: Notification Count badges & Seen status**
- Filter badge count display using `applications.filter(a => !a.read).length` and `certificates.filter(c => !c.read).length` in both sidebar navigation and mobile dropdowns.
- In Candidate Hub: when "View Profile" is clicked, trigger a helper `handleReviewCandidate(app)` that marks the application as `read` on the backend/state.
- In LMS Certificates tab: when the `activeTab` changes to `"certificates"`, collect all unread certificates and call `/api/certificates` (PUT) to mark them as `read`.

##### **Issue 3: Sticky Sidebar**
- Update the sidebar wrapper classes to use Tailwind stickiness: `className="hidden lg:flex w-64 flex-shrink-0 flex-col sticky top-[100px] self-start"`. This anchors the sidebar in the viewport alongside long scrolling pages.

##### **Issue 4: Custom Alert & Confirm Modals**
- Introduce a state-driven `modalConfig` state:
  - `{ type: "alert" | "confirm", title, message, onConfirm, onCancel }`
- Define `showAlert(msg, title)` and `showConfirm(msg, title)` wrappers that return Promises.
- Replace browser default `alert(...)` with `showAlert(...)`.
- Replace browser default `confirm(...)` with `await showConfirm(...)` in all asynchronous delete/action handlers.
- Render the custom dialog markup nicely with backdrop blurs (`backdrop-blur-sm`), a dark slate background, and standard button layouts.

##### **Issue 5: Academy Module Input Validation**
- In the "Publish New Training Module" section:
  - Change the order input tag type from `number` to `text`.
  - Add text validation `onChange={(e) => setModId(e.target.value.replace(/\D/g, ""))}` to ensure alphabet letters and symbols are stripped out of the input values and state before being submitted.

##### **Issue 6: Detailed Description Scrollbar Removal**
- In the "Incubated Brands" input form, add the `no-scrollbar` class to the Detailed Description textarea tag:
  `className="... resize-none no-scrollbar"`.

